    a: "The right answer for a Cockapoo is a clean, single named-protein, grain-free recipe to start with — because as a crossbreed you don't yet know which parent's sensitivities your pup inherited, so you keep the ingredient list simple and watch how they react. Forthglade is our all-round pick: its cold-pressed dry food (73–75% AADF) and wet trays (77–88%) are grain-free and gentle, the small-breed pellet suits a Cockapoo's smaller jaw, and being all-life-stage there's no diet switch as your pup matures. For fresh, whole-food nutrition with portions matched to your pup's weight, Butternut Box (93–94% AADF) and Years (95%) are excellent — and their omega-rich recipes feed that Poodle-inherited curly coat. Favour turkey or fish over chicken if your pup shows any itching, since chicken is a common Cocker-side trigger. Pooch & Mutt is the best-value grain-free kibble, though it's a chicken recipe, so check tolerance first."
  - q: "Why do Cockapoo puppies need special feeding?"
