  - q: "Are Cockapoo puppies prone to ear infections?"
    a: "Yes — it's one of the traits most likely to come through from the Cocker Spaniel side. Long, pendulous, hairy ears trap moisture, and food allergy is a leading driver of the inflammation that blocks and infects those ear canals. The most protective dietary move is a grain-free, single novel-protein recipe that avoids common triggers (grains, chicken, beef, dairy). If your pup starts head-shaking, scratching at its ears or you notice a smell, food is one of the first things to review — alongside keeping the ears clean, dry and the inner hair managed by your groomer."
  - q: "Is grain-free food good for Cockapoo puppies?"
