<p>Across all of it, three rules matter most for a Cockapoo: <strong>start simple and watch</strong> — a limited, single-protein, grain-free base so any reaction points to a clear cause; <strong>protect the ears</strong> by leaning grain-free and clean-protein, and keeping them dry and groomed; and <strong>feed the coat</strong> with omega-3 so that curly coat stays glossy and mat-resistant. If ear trouble, itching, weight, coat condition or toileting changes noticeably and doesn't settle, book a vet check.</p>

